dcterms:creator: M. Mackey
L. Glass
dcterms:description: The Mackey-Glass equation is a delay differential equation used to model chaotic dynamics. It is characterized by parameters that influence its chaotic behavior and is often used in studies of nonlinear dynamics.
dcterms:title: Mackey-Glass Equation

dcterms:creator: K. Ikeda
H. Daido
O. Akimoto
dcterms:description: The Ikeda equation is a nonlinear delay differential equation that exhibits chaotic behavior. It is used to study the dynamics of systems with time delays and is significant in the field of chaos theory.
dcterms:title: Ikeda Equation
